B
\mathbb{P}(A \cap B) = \mathbb{P}(A) \mathbb{P}(B)
\mathbb{P}(A \cup B) = \mathbb{P}(A) + \mathbb{P}(B) - \mathbb{P}(A \cap B) = 1 -(1-\mathbb{P}(A))(1-\mathbb{P}(B)))
T_X
X
\mathbb{P}( \lnot T_X \land \lnot T_Y \land \lnot T_Z) = \mathbb{P}( \lnot T_X ) \mathbb{P}( \lnot T_Y ) \mathbb{P}( \lnot T_Z) = (1 - \mathbb{P}( T_X))(1 - \mathbb{P}( T_Y))(1 - \mathbb{P}( T_Z))
\mathbb{P}( \lnot T_X \land \lnot T_Y \land \lnot T_Z) = (1-0.4)(1-0.3)(1-0.2) = 0.336
T_X \land T_Y \land T_Z
0.4 \times 0.3 \times 0.2 = 0.024
